hamate bone","A ligament connecting the hamate to the pisiform","A tendon attachment site on the hamate bone","A bony projection on the dorsal side of the hamate bone"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct description of the hook of hamate is that it is a \u003Cstrong\u003Ebony projection on the palmar side of the hamate bone\u003C/strong\u003E. This projection serves as an attachment point for ligaments and tendons in the hand, contributing to the stability and function of the wrist and hand.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA nerve passageway between the carpal tunnel and the hamate bone\u003C/strong\u003E - The hook of hamate is not involved in forming a nerve passageway\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA ligament connecting the hamate to the pisiform\u003C/strong\u003E - While ligaments connect various carpal bones, the hook of hamate itself is not a ligament\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA tendon attachment site on the hamate bone\u003C/strong\u003E - Although tendons attach near the hook, the hook itself is a bony projection\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA bony projection on the dorsal side of the hamate bone\u003C/strong\u003E - The hook is located on the palmar side, not the dorsal side\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The hook of hamate is a bony projection on the palmar side of the hamate bone.","The hamate bone is one of the carpal bones located in the wrist.","The hook of hamate serves as an attachment point for ligaments and tendons in the hand."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59067"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18127"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59067","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59067"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T00:25:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-13T00:38:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10841"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73597"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving inf